last_episode_to_air.overview: Tonight's the night. Brooke will finally reveal who she has chosen to do life with. But first, the final two must meet Brooke's nearest and dearest for a few hard home truths.

name: The Bachelorette
overview: Australian version of the reality series where an eligible bachelorette must find true love among a group of guys, one rose at a time.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Having won the nation's heart in The Bachelor Australia 2014, Sam Frost will be looking for love again as Australia's first ever Bachelorette. Will she have more luck in love the second time around?

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Season two follows the once-in-a lifetime journey of 28-year-old Victorian journalist Georgia Love, as she begins a desperate true love story of her own.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Having won the nation’s heart in The Bachelor Australia, Sam Frost will be looking for love again as Australia’s first Bachelorette

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: As the single dates kick off, Sam takes her chosen bachelor on the ultimate guy's first date. Also, on the first group date, Sam asks the bachelors to take a leap of faith for her.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: Having won the nation's heart in The Bachelor Australia 2014, Sam Frost will be looking for love again as Australia's first ever Bachelorette. Will she have more luck in love the second time around?

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: As the competition between the bachelors continues to heat up, alone time with Georgia is vital. How will the bachelors find new and creative ways to stand out from the crowd?

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Honouring the golden age of romance, Georgia picks her date up in an Aston Martin before enjoying a harbour cruise on a beautiful old boat. Will sparks fly or will he be friend-zoned?

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview: Georgia takes her final two bachelors away to the tropical metropolis of Singapore, where one man will walk away heartbroken and the other with the love of his life.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: Season two follows the once-in-a lifetime journey of 28-year-old Victorian journalist Georgia Love, as she begins a desperate true love story of her own.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: The season of romance continues when Sophie Monk embarks on her journey to find love with one of Australia's most eligible bachelors.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Sophie chooses one lucky man to take on the highly coveted first single date of the season. At the cocktail party, the men continue to do their best to impress Sophie and secure a rose.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: In a group date like no other, Sophie's family go undercover to get unfiltered access to the men. At the cocktail party, the men pull out all the stops but will it be enough to secure a rose?

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: It's time to separate the boys from the men as the bachelors compete in the Real Man Games. Later, at the cocktail party, some of the men open up to Sophie for the first time.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Sophie takes one lucky Bachelor for a day of old-fashioned romance. Later, the group date sees the intensity taken up a notch in an ultra-competitive game of bicycle polo.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Sophie takes one lucky suitor on a New York themed date. At the cocktail party, one Bachelor makes a wild accusation while a game of truth or dare leaves Sophie speechless.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: As the TV Week Logie Awards near, Eric, Erica and Nikki prepare their campaigns to secure individual Gold Logie nominations. Meanwhile, will Jack’s absence put his relationship with Lily on the rocks?

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Sophie’s Bachelors are split into two teams and brave the waves in a lively sailing race. On the single date, Sophie takes one bachelor on a group date: just them and eight adorable puppies.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Sophie puts the remaining Bachelors’ compatibility to the test with help from a Matching Scientist. On the single date, Sophie takes one city slicker Bachelor out of his comfort zone into the country.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: After weeks of being the one in control, it’s time for Sophie to be the one under pressure as she ventures all over Australia in order to meet the family and friends of the four remaining Bachelors.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Ready to find her one true love, Bachelorette Ali Oetjen is putting her heart on the line once more, hoping to meet Mr Right among the 18 eligible bachelors all vying for her heart.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: After an impressive first night meeting at the mansion, Ali already has her eye on a few favourites, so she arranges two big dates to get to know them better.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: It's time to strap on your sandals and breastplates, this episode is going Gladiator for a group date. The Bachelors will race and wrestle for some alone time. Who will be the lucky guy?

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: On the single date, Ali and her chosen Bachelor head to the river for an afternoon of wakeboarding, but it is the chemistry between these two that makes the biggest waves.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Ali is starting to separate the men from the boys. One lucky bachelor gets to enjoy a romantic single date and later on a group date, the boys must pull out their smoothest moves.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: With things starting to get serious, one Bachelor works up a sweat to impress. Later on a group date, the boy’s survivor skills are put to the test.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: Sharing special moments with two Bachelors on their home soil has Ali on cloud nine, however on the final two hometown visits, not all goes to plan.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: The Bachelorette Australia is back and Angie Kent is here to find love! There are puppies, bouquets of flowers, a throne, silver platters, lots of eligible men and... her brother?

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: The first single date of the series sees one very lucky Bachelor join Angie for very special 24 hours of intimate glamping in the wild. And a drama-filled cocktail party leaves the boys speechless.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Angie organises a date combining two of her favourite things – Bachelors and rescue dogs. At the cocktail party things get tense when one Bachelor breaks the boy code.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Angie's BFF takes the boys to a bachelorette party to get to know the men who are hoping to steal her bestie's heart. At the cocktail party, there are secret kisses, tears and pissed-off bachelors.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: After a group date where the boys are asked to write and perform a stand-up comedy routine, tensions rise and jealousy flairs at the cocktail party as the boys continue to vie for time with Angie.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: There is nothing more important to Angie than family and tonight Angie introduces her Top 10 suiters to her parents in an emotional group date.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: A misunderstanding at the Cocktail Party leads to a major disruption as two Bachelors have a heated confrontation with one Bachelor threatening to walk.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Osher reveals that the Bachelors will be taking part in a Bachelorette Quiz to test that they have been paying attention to their Bachelorette during their time together. How will the boys perform?

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: For the single date, Angie takes one Bachelor to explore their obvious physical chemistry. Later the cocktail party is replaced by The Last Supper where secrets and lies are revelaed.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: Angie heads home to meet the friends and family of her remaining four suitors... welcome to hometowns. At the Rose Ceremony, it is crunch time for Angie who must make some hard decisions.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview: With the Rose Ceremony decision weighing heavily on her mind, Angie needs to get to the bottom of some concerns that came up at hometowns and clear the air once and for all.

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview: In this raw and emotional finale, kisses will be shared and tears shed, hearts will be broken and declarations of love will be made, but who has made the greatest impression on Angie?

episodes.name: Premiere
episodes.overview: Sisters Elly and Becky Miles begin their search for love together side by side. This season will boast double the dates, double the fun and double the romance. Love has never looked so bright,

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Bachelorette Elly takes one suitor on a daring single date that has them hanging over a vast mountaneous chasm, while sister Becky spends some quality time at the mansion with a charismatic Bachelor.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Chemistry sizzles as Becky and a beau open up about life, love and hopes for the future. The Bachelors are unhappy with one of their own, and it all comes to a head at the Cocktail Party.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Brooke Blurton takes center stage as the first Indigenous bi-sexual woman on The Bachelorette Australia. Brooke is eager to greet both the men and women vying to win over her heart.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: It's the pivotal photoshoot date where contenders are thrown together in photo worthy scenarios. Plus, Tensions between two contenders continues to bubble over, leaving one clearly coming out on top.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Brooke takes a contender on a single date that's straight out of a movie. Then, the gloves come off on the group date as one of Brooke's love interests is targeted by some of the other contestants.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: In a single date that's all about self-care, Brooke cosies up to one of her suitors and leaves our Bachelorette knowing exactly where they stand with her. Then, the Cocktail Party with a twist!

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: We're another step closer to finding out who has secured Brooke's heart. One lucky suitor's persistence pays off, not once but twice, leaving the others question their connection with Brooke.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: A skyscraper date leaves Brooke feeling on top of the world, before a human lie detector sees it all come crashing down. At the cocktail party, tensions rise and some hard-hitting truths are revealed.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: It's Mardi Gras madness, with two teams pitted against each other to win time with Brooke on the group date. At the cocktail party, one contender clears the air with Brook in hopes of receiving a rose.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: One lucky contender is the first to score a second single date, while true intentions of the contenders are revealed on a play-inspired group date, featuring some little helpers.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Brooke shows her vulnerability in the final group date. Then, just like that, Hometowns are here! Brooke's final four introduce her to their nearest and dearest with mixed results.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: The time has come for Brooke's final three contenders to woo her, From an adventure-filled day to a performance of a lifetime, who will pull out all stops to get closer to our Bachelorette?

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview: Tonight's the night. Brooke will finally reveal who she has chosen to do life with. But first, the final two must meet Brooke's nearest and dearest for a few hard home truths.
